{
  "texts": [
    "Based on a selfbuilt comparable corpus containing machine translations, human translations, and target-language originals across multiple genres, lexical diversity as a proxy of simplification was analyzed.",
    "The results show that simplification is found in both human-and machine-translated government documents and academic abstracts when compared with English original texts.",
    "However, in terms of contemporary novels, simplification is only verified in machine translations, while human translations are found to have no significant difference from English original texts.",
    "More importantly, machine translations (Google Translate and DeepL) across the three genres have no significant difference between each other and are significantly more simplified than human translations.",
    "In addition, the variable genre remarkably moderates the lexical diversity of different text varieties."
  ]
}